@notice Update the designated withdrawal wait period. Required to be greater than the
minimum.
@param newWaitPeriod - The new wait period for withdrawals.

@notice Check a given subscriber's balance for a given asset.
@param subscriber - The subscriber whose balance we're checking.
@param asset - The asset belonging to the subscriber's account.

@notice Check if a given nonce for a given subscriber has already expired.
@param subscriber - The subscriber whose nonces we're checking.
@param nonce - The nonce index number.

@notice Anyone can call this method to check the timestamp of withdrawal requests submitted.
Providers should use this before initiating (or continuing) a state channel session to check
whether they should pull support for a given asset for a given subscriber.
@dev If the value is zero (0) then there's no open request.
@param subscriber - Subscriber whose requests we are checking.
@param asset - The asset potentially being withdrawn.

@notice Subscribers use this method to deposit allowed assets into their account. Callers
should have already approved this contract for the deposit amount. Funds are spent via
state channel redemptions in the claim() method.
@param _asset - The asset to be deposited.
@param amount - The amount of the given asset to be deposited via ERC20 transfer.

@notice Subscribers call this method to initiate a withdrawal from their account. The
withdrawal will be for the full amount remaining when completeWithdrawal() is called. Any
in-flight state channels will still be able to be closed out by the provider using claim().
@param asset - The asset for which the withdrawal request will be submitted.

@notice Subscribers who have initiated a withdrawal and waited for the set
withdrawalWaitPeriod can complete the withdrawal with this method. All remaining funds in
the account will be drained and transferred to the subscriber (the caller).
@param asset - The asset for which the withdrawal request was submitted.

@notice Providers use this method to close out a state channel interaction with a given
subscriber. The subscriber's address is derived from their signature, which indicates
approval for the provider withdrawal.
@dev Signature packet: (provider, nonce, asset, amount).
@param nonce - The nonce index number for this interaction.
@param asset - The address of the asset being claimed.
@param amount - The amount of the given asset being claimed.
@param signature - The subscriber's signature on the aforementioned parameters (as well
as the provider who gets to claim).

@notice Helper method for splitting a signature and doing ecrecover to get the
signature's signer address.
@param message - 32-byte message data.
@param signature - Signature bytes.
